        <name>10.1.2.15 Dividing complex numbers</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Convert&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\[\frac{{@n1@} + {@n2@}\,{@%i@}}{{@n3@} + {@n4@}\,{@%i@}}\]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;into the form \(p+q\,{@%i@}\), where \(p\) and \(q\) are real. Input your answer, in the form &lt;span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier, monospace;"&gt;p + q*i&lt;/span&gt;, in the box below:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\(\displaystyle \frac{{@n1@} + {@n2@}\,{@%i@}}{{@n3@} + {@n4@}\,{@%i@}} =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[[feedback:Result]]&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;Multiplying the top and bottom by the conjugate of the denominator gives&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\[ \frac{\ {@n1@} + {@n2@}\,{@%i@}\ }{\ {@n3@} + {@n4@}\,{@%i@}\ } \times \frac{\ {@n3@} - {@n4@}\,{@%i@}\ }{\ {@n3@} - {@n4@}\,{@%i@}\ } = \frac{\ {@n1*n3@} + {@n2*n3@}\,{@%i@} - {@n1*n4@}\,{@%i@} - {@n2*n4@}\,{@%i@}^2\ }{\ {@n3*n3@} + {@n3*n4@}\,{@%i@} - {@n4*n3@}\,{@%i@} - {@n4*n4@}\,{@%i@}^2\ },\]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and because \({@%i@}^2= -1\) we obtain&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\[ \frac{\ {@n1*n3@} + {@n2*n3@}\,{@%i@} - {@n1*n4@}\,{@%i@} - {@n2*n4@}\,{@%i@}^2\ }{\ {@n3*n3@} + {@n3*n4@}\,{@%i@} - {@n4*n3@}\,{@%i@} - {@n4*n4@}\,{@%i@}^2\ } = \frac{\ {@tempc@}\ }{\ {@n3*n3 + n4*n4@}\ }={@correctanswer@}.\]&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
